textBeforeTable: Nagydíj: Hungary.  Joy.  Here's the provisional grid for the 2015 Magyar F1 Quals: Hungary 2015 --> border="0" alt="Other F1 Stuff" title="Other F1 Stuff" /> align="left" height="48" width="48" July 25, 2015 Hide Comments | Add Comment Posted by: ReallyBored at July 28, 2015 12:39 PM (ulGxe) 5 And wow.  That was great race.  Posted by: flatdarkmars at July 27, 2015 07:50 PM (HNK5u) 4 Most enjoyable F1 race since Bahrain last year, I think. Posted by: Wonderduck at July 27, 2015 11:13 AM (jGQR+) 3 RB, watch it.  It's worth the time.  GD, it was like someone dropped a grenade in a trench.  The scrambling was awesome! Posted by: GreyDuck at July 27, 2015 07:47 AM (/zxpg) 2 The Unstoppable Team kept entirely off the podium? Did I read that right? What a mess of a race, it looks like. Posted by: ReallyBored at July 27, 2015 05:26 AM (DOcWF) 1 Wow.  I'm glad I didn't delete the race sight unseen because, well, Hungary
textAfterTable: For what seemed the first time all season, the Mercedes were actually forced to use their soft tires in Q1, lest they be bumped from quals altogether.  There's a huge performance gap between the soft and hards this time, two seconds or so... it's usually half that.  Other than that, though, nothing particularly exciting went on.  Oh sure, Red Bull seems to have made good use of the past three weeks, looking awfully racy as a result, but with Merc domination it all seems somewhat futile. Probably the highlight of the session was Fernando Alonso's car failing towards the start of Q2.  Feeling like he had a chance to make it to Q3, it took his lame car as far as it could go... just short of the pit-in.  When it stopped?  He hopped out and pushed.  Soon, he had an entourage. Yes, that's Alonso waving to the fans while steering his car with one hand while at a fast jog in a firesuit on a 95 degree day with high humidity.  Yes, that's also a cheeky trackworker waving to the crowd, too.  It almost pains me to point out that the second his car came to a halt on-track it was ineligible to continue the session, but that's just me. So.  Race tomorrow morning.  F1U! sometime after.  Then the summer break, one month until the next race.  See ya
